<doc id="851022" wikidata="Q2199558" url="?curid=851022" title="Aerts">
<text>The Aerts (also spelled &quot;Aarts&quot;) was a Dutch automobile manufactured in 1899; a small number of cars are known to have been built at Dongen, but little else seems to be known about the marque.

The manufacturer also advertised as &quot;Neerlandia, the first Dutch car&quot;, although &quot;Groninger&quot; and Eysink were earlier.

