<doc id="851153" wikidata="Q7045343" url="?curid=851153" title="Noah (gaur)">
<text>Noah was the name of the first cloned &quot;gaur&quot;. He was cloned and gestated in the womb of a cow named Bessie. Gaurs are listed as a vulnerable species on the IUCN Red List. Noah was delivered on January 8, 2001, but he died within just 48 hours of dysentery on January 10, 2001. Noah&#x27;s condition was monitored by Dr. Jonathan Hill and his teammates in Iowa. The process used to clone Noah was nuclear transfer.

==References==

